-- 02_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
WITH approved_returns AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT ON (item_id) 
        item_id
    FROM returns
    WHERE status = 'approved'
    ORDER BY item_id, return_date DESC
)
SELECT 
    COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized') AS category_name,
    COUNT(oi.item_id) AS total_items_sold,
    COUNT(ar.item_id) AS total_items_returned,
    CASE 
        WHEN COUNT(oi.item_id) > 0 
        THEN ROUND(COUNT(ar.item_id)::DECIMAL / COUNT(oi.item_id), 4)
        ELSE 0 
    END AS return_rate
FROM order_items oi
JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id
LEFT JOIN categories c ON p.category_id = c.category_id
LEFT JOIN approved_returns ar ON oi.item_id = ar.item_id
GROUP BY c.name
ORDER BY return_rate DESC;
